Package com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.adt.symbolTable.tree

Interface BST<Key extends Comparable<Key>,Value>

Type Parameters:
Key - the type of keys, which must be Comparable.
Value - the type of values associated with the keys.
All Superinterfaces:
ImmutableSymbolTable<Key,Value>, ST<Key,Value>
All Known Subinterfaces:
BstDetail<Key,Value>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BSTOptimisedDeletion, BSTSimple
public interface BST<Key extends Comparable<Key>,Value> extends ST<Key,Value>
Interface defining the core methods for a Binary Search Tree (BST). A BST is a data structure that stores key-value pairs in a sorted manner such that for every node, keys in the left subtree are less than the node's key, and keys in the right subtree are greater.
